    <section id="id5936795">
      <title>Assessment</title>
      <para id="id1172373080637">LEARNING OUTCOME 3: INTERPRETING HISTORY – The learner will be able to interpret aspects of history</para>
      <para id="id7688967">3.1 Be aware of more than  one view of the past</para>
      <para id="id4082956">Understand that different views of the same issue may be right or wrong.</para>
      <para id="id7962269">3.2 Distinguish between fact and opinion.</para>
      <para id="id7448943">Distinguish between a fact and an opinion.</para>
      <para id="id6101235">Is able to access information from maps, charts, diagrams and graphs.</para>
      <para id="id6117090">3.3 Reconstruct the past</para>
      <para id="id5279158">Is able to reconstruct events and understand how people feel about them.</para>
    </section>
